-- Ukraine's Energoatom to Get $2 Billion Russian Loan, Radio Liberty Reports
-- Daryna Krasnolutska
-- 2010-06-17T08:37:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/ukraine-s-energoatom-to-get-2-billion-russian-loan-radio-liberty-reports.html

          
          
             Ukraine’s atomic-plant operator DP
NAEK Energoatom will receive a $2 billion loan from a Russian
bank to build two reactors, Radio Liberty reported, citing the
head of President  Viktor Yanukovych ’s staff, Serhiy Lyovochkin.  
 Energoatom will take as much as $500 million out of $2
billion this year, Lyovochkin said, according to Radio Liberty.  
 Lyovochkin also confirmed that Ukraine’s government has
already received a $2 billion loan from Russia’s VTB bank to
cover the state budget deficit, Radio Liberty said. He declined
to give any details, citing “commercial secret,” according to
the radio.  
